Distribution .
Pseudoscalibregma parvum
has been recorded from East Greenland , Jan Mayen , Spitsbergen , Norwegian Sea and Kara Sea, in depths from 20 to 1715 m (this study;
Furreg 1925
;
Støp-Bowitz 1948
;
Jirkov 2001
;
Bakken et al. 2010
). The shallowest records are all Arctic, from East Greenland and the Kara Sea. On the shelf around the island of Jan Mayen some shallow records, from 109 m , are from an area with mixed North Atlantic and Arctic water masses with temperatures down to below 0°C (
Bakken et al. 2010
). In the Norwegian Sea there are a few records in shelf areas, but most records are from 600 m and deeper, where water temperatures are below 0°C (
Fig. 7
A).
